reviews.review_text:
Flawless Nice set, great sound, CM
OBAMA!
11-15-87 Nice show. Stellar sound once again from Charlie.
Great show Excellent sound, the Scarlet-fire is up-beat and rockin, killer Hes Gone->Drums.
Great Show And, NYLifer... 6 years later, still think Obama is good? Hahahahaaa
Nice Scarlet>Fire Nice Scarlet>Fire, kind of reminds me of 3-27-89.  BTW, kochman, 8 years later, Obama's looking pretty fuckin' good compared to what we have now.

Excellent Show Excellent show capping off a strong three-night stand at the Long Beach Arena.  The first night we danced for four hours and the clouds opened up outside - it was clear and the ground was soaked when we walked out.  Night 3, the boys pulled out the stops and delivered a kind Scarlet > Fire, and then an incendiary combo of Other One > Dew > Around & Around > Watchtower.

Oh, and to the cynic posting earlier, yes, Obama was a great president - vastly better than the orange man-baby with the impulse control and emotional balance of a spoiled toddler currently sitting in the Oval Office.

Really Nice Show.... ..and fantastic sound complements of CM.  Out here at the beach on a beautiful day, put my hat over my face and and cranked up West LA, felt like I was right back in a dark auditorium dancin away.  Looking forward the the 3nd set!

Excellent Show  >Fire on the Mountain> This was the beginning of a run from    87 - 90 that was truly amazing.
Good Vibes
